                                    <rect key="frame" x="8" y="363.5" width="398" height="93.5"/>
                                    <string key="text">One-Time Certificate (OTC) is a maximum-length key that is used to encrypt your message. 
It is far better than a password since it is 256 bits in length, you don't need to remember it and it is used only once.
Moreover, you can set an expiration time and it will be erased from the device and the message will be unreadable any more.</string>
                                    <fontDescription key="fontDescription" type="system" pointSize="13"/>
